# HarmonyOS Cross-App Communication Rules

## Shared Protocol

- Keep cross-app command names and payload shapes in `shared/ets/bridge/AppBridgeTypes.ets`.
- Use the shared `BridgeCommand`, `BridgeParameters`, `BridgeResponse`, and `AppTarget` types when building Want payloads or handling app-service requests.
- Prefer importing shared modules through `entry/src/main/ets/_shared/...` after the app scripts link `shared/ets/` into the app.

## Want Construction

- App-to-app page launches should use typed Want parameters and include:
  - `command`
  - `sourceBundleName`
  - `sourceModuleName`
  - `sourceAbilityName`
  - `timestamp` or `startedAt`
- Use `FLAG_START_WITHOUT_TIPS` only for flows that already match the workspace launch model.
- Do not rely on untyped ad hoc command strings when a `BridgeCommand` value exists.

## AppServiceExtensionAbility

- App bridge services must remain small dispatchers:
  - parse `want.parameters` into `BridgeParameters`
  - switch or branch by `BridgeCommand`
  - call `context.startAbility` or a focused platform API
  - terminate the service after handling the request
- Do not put screen business logic inside `AppBridgeService.ets`.
- Keep desktop shortcut visibility commands explicit and typed; do not overload `OPEN_ENTRY`.

## Ownership

- `shared/ets/bridge/` owns protocol definitions and Want helpers.
- Each `app-*` still owns its app identity, labels, module names, ability names, and service-specific platform behavior.
- Shared modules should be promoted to a HAR package only after the symlink-based `_shared` flow is stable across apps.
